race.comment: MY BELLA VISTA (8) sat off the speed before asserting her class on debut when an effortless winner over 1100m at Goulburn. From an in-form stable and no shock to see her take holding out again. TRIPLE PLAY (6) heavily supported on debut with J Mac aboard when defeating a small field as favourite over 1000m at Hawkesbury. Returned good figures on that occasion and she can get the job done again. ROSE OF DUBAI (2) resumes from a lengthy break. Gave them a galloping lesson on debut from the outside draw when an emphatic winner over 1200m at Newcastle. Fitted with the two trials and she gets a much better set-up today. Top three player. MISS FLEETWOOD (7) deep into her prep and holding her form well. Speared across from the wide gate when a game second over 1300m at Hawkesbury in stronger company. Will roll forward again and figure prominently.
